name: facilities-for-antenna-and-rcs-measurements-4-5-5
notes: Purpose: The Radar and Antenna Systems Division conducts measurements of the characteristics of antenna systems and avionics systems installed on partial to full-size airframes. These measurements are conducted from outdoor ranges at the Facilities for Antenna and RCS Measurements (FARM).  Function: The outdoor ranges are configurable for several illuminator/test items at distances up to 1500 feet away. Measurements are made on antennas and avionics systems installed on partial model airframes or full-scale aircraft configurations to determine the effects of the airframe on their characteristics.  Capabilities:   Evaluation of both antennas and complete avionics systems installed on or in a full-size aircraft Remotely controlled illuminator towers can be positioned up to 1,500 feet away Measurement of antenna radiation patterns, gain, phase, VSWR, and antenna-to&#172;-antenna isolation Desired and jamming signal sources can be positioned for the technical evaluation of the avionics systems installed in the host airframe Partial full scale mock-up measurements and communications antenna evaluations Analog/ digital antenna pattern recording Frequency range of 20 MHz to 20 GHz Rain erosion/impact measurements Computational Electromagnetics Modeling  Unique Assets List:   Full Scale Aircraft Antenna Ranges Full Scale Aircraft Antenna Tower Multi-configured antenna range Anechoic Chambers (pyramidal and rectangular) Integrated channel multiplexing high-speed acquisition system Software for automated antenna measurements 10,000 pound maximum load azimuth-over elevation positioner 750 pound maximum load model tower mounted on an adjacent railroad track Remotely controlled illuminator towers Various RF Test Equipment Model Aircraft Aerodynamic steel counterbalanced rotating arm Radome Electromagnetic Interference Tool.
title: Facilities for Antenna and RCS Measurements (4.5.5)
